## Copilot Agent Task: Analyse EhCache RMI Usage (Read-Only — Do NOT modify any files)

### Goal
Scan the entire codebase and produce a structured analysis of how EhCache with RMI 
replication is currently used. Do not suggest fixes or write any code yet.

### What to look for

#### 1. Configuration files (check all of these patterns)
- Any `ehcache.xml` or `ehcache*.xml` files — note location and every <cache> block inside
- Any `.properties` or `.yml`/`.yaml` files referencing ehcache, RMI, or replication
- Any `@Bean` methods returning `CacheManager`, `EhCacheManagerFactoryBean`, 
  or `net.sf.ehcache.*` types
- Any XML Spring context files (`applicationContext*.xml`) referencing ehcache beans

#### 2. Plain Java wiring (non-Spring)
- Any class that calls `CacheManager.create()` or `CacheManager.getInstance()` directly
- Any class implementing `CacheEventListener` or extending `CacheEventListenerAdapter`
- Any use of `RMICacheReplicatorFactory`, `RMIBootstrapCacheLoaderFactory`, 
  or `RMIAsynchronousCacheReplicator`
- Any class that calls `cache.put()`, `cache.remove()`, `cache.get()` directly 
  on an `net.sf.ehcache.Cache` object (not via Spring abstraction)

#### 3. For each cache found, extract
- Cache name
- Is it configured in XML or Java?
- Is RMI replication enabled? (look for replicatePuts, replicateRemovals etc.)
- What type of data does it hold? (check usage sites — is it a token, config, user data?)
- Where is it written to (put/replace)?
- Where is it read from (get)?
- Is there any TTL / expiry configured?

### Output format
Respond ONLY in this structure — one block per cache found:

---
CACHE: <cache name>
CONFIG LOCATION: <file and line>
WIRING STYLE: Spring Bean | Plain Java | XML only
RMI REPLICATION: Yes | No | Unknown
